Wai Yan Moe is an Intern Software Engineer with 2 months of commercial internship experience. Their core expertise lies in Mobile Development, particularly with Flutter, and they demonstrate strong foundational knowledge in Artificial Intelligence and Computer Vision. Through academic and hackathon projects, Wai Yan has applied these skills to develop solutions such as a Real-Time Traffic Prediction App utilizing Artificial Intelligence and Computer Vision for traffic density prediction and route optimization, and an AI-powered Vietnamese water puppetry application built with Flutter during a 28-hour hackathon.
Technically, Wai Yan is proficient in a diverse range of programming languages including HTML, CSS, Javascript, Nodejs, PHP, Python, Java, and Kotlin. They have hands-on experience with mobile development frameworks like Flutter and Android SDK, and are adept with databases such as MySQL, Firebase, Mongodb, and MicrosoftSQL. Their DevOps and cloud exposure includes Docker and Firebase, complemented by development tools like Git, XAMPP, Eclipse, and Android Studio. Wai Yan's domain knowledge spans Web Development, Mobile Development, Artificial Intelligence, and Computer Vision.